reviewText: I've had this DVD for about two years, and, out of over 125 workout DVD's that I own, this is my absolute favorite ab workout. I never get sick of doing the workouts on here because of Cathe's wonderful personality and encouraging attitude.When I do the workouts on here on a regular basis, I also notice fewer lower back aches and pains.  Cathe really works not just your abs, but your entire core -- the entire abdominal region, as well as the lower back.The three workouts are definitely advanced, but you can modify, and they require the use of a stability ball and a medicine ball.Highly recommended!
Title: N/A

reviewText: This is about my 7th workout of Cathes and it's great.  It's tough but it's going to give you amazing results if you do it consistantly.  On the DVD there are three different types of workouts.  There is classic floor work, abdominal workout using a stability ball and also a workout with a stability ball and medicine ball.  It's fun and gets easier over time.All of these ab workouts are going to tone you up and flatten you out (if you do a lot of cardio too).  She is a great instructor and she cues well so you know what's coming up next.  If you want a toned tummy, you need to eat right, do cardio and use this DVD for a fantastic ab workout that you will feel.  It's great.

reviewText: This is definitely for the advanced exerciser, very tough concentrated ab exercises, lots of time consuming planks.It took me a while before I could effectively do this workout.I had to drop a good ten pounds (my stomach) to be able to do all the exercises effectively, without injuring my lower back, or over straining my wrist, etc.This is not for the faint of heart, and you really need to be in peak shape to be able to do this right, without injuring yourself. (At least from my experience, so head's up!)

reviewText: I remember this workout when I subscribed to Cable TV. I recorded this on my antique VHS player and it got all chewed up. Not having cable anymore, I discovered this DVD on line and couldn't wait to buy it and start using it again. Again, it's very challenging and if you do not want a difficult challenge, this is not for you. I like a challenge, and Cathe's Core Max will definitely give it to you. It's tough, but that's what I like.

reviewText: This DVD has three different 20 minute core workouts.  Routine 1 uses no equipment, Routine 2 uses a stability ball, and Routine 3 uses a medicine ball and a stability ball.This is one of Cathe's best core workouts.Why I love this workout:**it's deceptively hard!  Even the no equipment routine is a killer.  Those rocket shoots and levitation moves get me every time.**the variety.  I don't like core work and I have to force myself to do it.  With the three very different routines, plus 3 pre-mixes that combine pieces of each routine, I will never tire of doing this DVD.**Cathe's encouragement.  I love hearing her say that even if you can't do a move like the levitation move completely, just the act of attempting the move works your core.**the 20 minute length of each routine.  This makes it easy to tack on the core work after doing another workout.If you want some fun and different core routines, you will like this DVD.
summary: Fun, versatile and effective core routines
